contributions.description:
We propose new detailed form  for conformal symmetry breaking effects in the relation between perturbative massless expressions for the e+ e-  annihilation Adler function, Bjorken sum rule for polarized DIS  (or neutrino DIS Gross-Llewellym Smith sum rule) in QCD. The validity of this new form is demonstrated at the new 5-loop level. Relations to radiative corrections to one of the formfatctors of  Axial Vector Vector triangle amplitude are reminded. Concrete consequences, which follow from our new foundations are studied in QCD, QED and in gauge theories with fermions in 16 1/2-N_f Banks-Zaks limit.  

